  <datafield tag="545" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Erich A. Walter was a faculty member at the University of Michigan for 53 years, beginning as an instructor of rhetoric in 1919 and ending as the Assistant to the President Harlan Hatcher and the Secretary of the University. He was also a very successful editor and author, his most popular works being "Essay Annual" and "A Pictorial History of the Great Lakes," which he co-authored with Harlan Hatcher.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This collection contains Walter's University related papers, including correspondence, research and projects, essays and speeches, and photographs used in and drafts of "A Pictorial History of the Great Lakes," in addition to papers related to Walter's work as an editor on "Essay Annual" and "Toward Today."</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="506" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection is open for research use.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="555" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Finding aid in the library.</subfield>
  </datafield>
